ce:section.ce:para:
The 2024-T3 aluminum alloy was used and the chemical composition was given in Table 1
                     . The aluminum alloy was cleaned in ethanol before use. Acid etching solution was composed of 250 g/L H2SO4, 250 g/L HNO3 and 50 g/L ferric sulfate. Etching step was operated at 50 °C for 10 min. A few tests were conducted at 25 °C to confirm that it was essential to perform the etching with high temperature. The experimental set-up preformed in the laboratory was carried out in a jacketed glass cylindrical vessel (diameter: 60 mm and height: 130 mm) with temperature monitoring and control (Fig. 1
                     ). A 20 mm diameter circular electrode made of aluminum alloy was placed in a tailor-made holder with an active area of 3.14 cm2. The holder was stirred at 800 rpm. For experiments under ultrasound irradiation, the holder containing aluminum was located opposite the ultrasonic source. To take account of previous works [28,33], the distance between the aluminum electrode and the ultrasonic source was studied from 5 cm to 1 cm. A titanium horn at 20 kHz was used as an ultrasonic source to transmit ultrasound to the liquid media (Sonics & Materials, Danbury USA). Acoustic power, measured by calorimetric method, was 70 W [34]. After etching, all samples were rinsed and dried before characterization.
